<section id="Section519936">
  <title>
<indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>item sites</primary>
      <secondary>by class code</secondary>
    </indexterm> <indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>class codes</primary>
      <secondary>item site details for</secondary>
    </indexterm>Item Sites by Class Code</title>
  <para>To view Item Sites by Class Code, select the "Item Sites by Class
  Code" option. The following screen will appear:</para>
  <para>
<screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/dspItemSitesByClassCode.png"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>Item Sites by Class Code</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot>
</para>
  <para>When displaying Item Sites by Class Code, you are presented with the
  following options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>All Class Codes</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Select to display Item Sites for all Class Codes.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Selected</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify Class Code whose Item Sites you want to display.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Pattern</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Enter a Class Code pattern to select a range of Class Codes.
        Refine your search using Regular Expressions.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry role="standard">
      <term>All Sites</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Select to display Item Sites by Class Code for all
        Sites.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry role="standard">
      <term>Selected</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify Site whose Item Sites by Class Code you want to
        display.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Show Inactive</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Select to display active as well as inactive Item Sites.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Item Sites</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Display lists Item Sites by Class Code, using the specified
        parameters.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>To the far right of the screen, the following buttons are
  available:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>CLOSE</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Closes the screen, returning you to the application
        desktop.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>QUERY</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Select to generate the display, using the specified
        parameters.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>PRINT</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Runs the report associated with this screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>Right-clicking on an Item Site in the Item Sites list enables you to
  select from the following menu options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickViewItemSite)"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickEditItemSite)"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickViewInventoryAvailability)"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickIssueCountTag)"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../widgets/xtreewidget.xml" xpointer="element(xtreewidget.menu.exportcontents)"/>
  </variablelist>
</section>
